<div class="section" id="rchainSection">
    <h1>The Power of the Cooperative</h1>
    <p>The purpose of RChain is to provide its members discounted access to a decentralized, public computation platform. RChain supports the development of on-chain tools for governance and online communications that promote collaboration at scale. Our mission is to provide a platform that promotes the proliferation of social coordination technologies.</p>
</div>

<div class="section" id="posSection">
    <div class="textWrapper">
        <p>Becoming a member requires a nonrefundable, one-time $20 fee. To maintain your membership, you have to spend at least $10 in fees once the platform launches. You are then eligible for a rebate each year based on usage (think <a href="https://www.rei.com/member-thanks" target="_blank">REI</a>).</p>
        <p>During registration you’ll have the option of joining our Discord community. Once you’re signed up, we’ll communicate with you through member newsletters to provide voting information and other essential notifications.</p>
        <p>RChain follows the International Co-operative Alliance principles. To learn more about what this means, read their <a href="https://www.ica.coop/sites/default/files/publication-files/ica-guidance-notes-en-310629900.pdf" target="_blank">Guidance Notes</a>.</p>
